I would like to be able to select a region and hit a key or run something from the command panel to auto-indent the whole thing based on the indent level of the first line.

![indent-region](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/1476/92264/260262d8-65c6-11e2-8e99-e6661e9a23ed.gif)

@probablycorey pointed me in the direction of `suggestedIndentForBufferRow()` and when I get time i'll probably try using that in a function in my own atom config, but i think it's a generally useful feature.
